data.description: Experience the charm of this Boulder residence situated in the highly sought-after Table Mesa neighborhood. Upon entering, you will be greeted by an inviting living room filled with natural light streaming through the windows which face the front yard.  The kitchen has been partially updated with new countertops, backsplash, and flooring, and is equipped with stainless-steel appliances and ample cabinet space. Continue to the dining room where a glass door invites you to step out and enjoy the fully fenced backyard. The upper-level hosts three bedrooms and a full bathroom with a double sink vanity. On the lower level, relax in the second living room by the warmth of a wood-burning fireplace and enjoy the view to the backyard. This level also features a 3/4 bathroom, a flex room (non-conforming), and a laundry area with a side-by-side washer and dryer. Revel in the tranquility of the landscaped backyard that creates an ideal setting for relaxation and entertainment. This property is conveniently located near restaurants, grocery stores, and hiking trails. A quick drive away are the stunning natural destinations of Chautauqua Park, Eldorado Springs, NCAR, and the iconic Boulder Flatirons. Arrange for a tour of the property to experience its offerings firsthand.
